    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Insight:** After industry-median imputation, 39,244 postings have usable salary values and 33,232 postings remain missing salary. This increases the salary sample size compared with the original `ANALYSIS_SALARY` variable, which had 32,394 observed salary values.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Salary Missingness Bias Check\n",
        "\n",
        "This section checks whether salary availability still differs across important groups after using the imputed salary variable. This helps identify whether salary-based results may still be affected by missing salary patterns."
      ],
      "id": "2e4c0f0d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "message": false
      },
      "source": [
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| warning: false\n",
        "\n",
        "ai_job_ids = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT DISTINCT\n",
        "    ID AS job_id\n",
        "FROM raw_jobs_clean\n",
        "WHERE\n",
        "    LOWER(TITLE_CLEAN) LIKE '%machine learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(TITLE_CLEAN) LIKE '%artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(TITLE_CLEAN) LIKE '%ai engineer%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(TITLE_CLEAN) LIKE '%ml engineer%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(TITLE_CLEAN) LIKE '%generative ai%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(TITLE_CLEAN) LIKE '%llm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%machine learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%generative ai%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%large language model%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%llm%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%deep learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(BODY) LIKE '%natural language processing%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(SPECIALIZED_SKILLS_NAME) LIKE '%machine learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(SPECIALIZED_SKILLS_NAME) LIKE '%artificial intelligence%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(SPECIALIZED_SKILLS_NAME) LIKE '%deep learning%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(SPECIALIZED_SKILLS_NAME) LIKE '%natural language processing%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(SOFTWARE_SKILLS_NAME) LIKE '%pytorch%'\n",
        "    OR LOWER(SOFTWARE_SKILLS_NAME) LIKE '%tensorflow%'\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "ai_job_ids.createOrReplaceTempView(\"ai_job_ids\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "salary_missing_by_ai = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    CASE\n",
        "        WHEN a.job_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI-related'\n",
        "        ELSE 'Non-AI'\n",
        "    END AS career_type,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT r.ID) AS total_postings,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN r.ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NOT NULL\n",
        "             AND r.ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED > 0\n",
        "        THEN r.ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_available,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN r.ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "             OR r.ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "        THEN r.ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_missing,\n",
        "    ROUND(\n",
        "        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "            WHEN r.ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "                 OR r.ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "            THEN r.ID\n",
        "        END) / COUNT(DISTINCT r.ID) * 100,\n",
        "        2\n",
        "    ) AS missing_salary_percent\n",
        "FROM raw_jobs_clean r\n",
        "LEFT JOIN ai_job_ids a\n",
        "    ON r.ID = a.job_id\n",
        "GROUP BY\n",
        "    CASE\n",
        "        WHEN a.job_id IS NOT NULL THEN 'AI-related'\n",
        "        ELSE 'Non-AI'\n",
        "    END\n",
        "ORDER BY missing_salary_percent DESC\n",
        "\"\"\").toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "display(style_table(salary_missing_by_ai, {\n",
        "    \"total_postings\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_available\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_missing\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"missing_salary_percent\": \"{:.2f}%\"\n",
        "}))\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "salary_missing_by_remote = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    REMOTE_TYPE_NAME AS remote_type,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT ID) AS total_postings,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NOT NULL\n",
        "             AND ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED > 0\n",
        "        THEN ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_available,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "             OR ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "        THEN ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_missing,\n",
        "    ROUND(\n",
        "        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "            WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "                 OR ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "            THEN ID\n",
        "        END) / COUNT(DISTINCT ID) * 100,\n",
        "        2\n",
        "    ) AS missing_salary_percent\n",
        "FROM raw_jobs_clean\n",
        "WHERE REMOTE_TYPE_NAME IS NOT NULL\n",
        "GROUP BY REMOTE_TYPE_NAME\n",
        "ORDER BY missing_salary_percent DESC\n",
        "\"\"\").toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "display(style_table(salary_missing_by_remote, {\n",
        "    \"total_postings\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_available\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_missing\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"missing_salary_percent\": \"{:.2f}%\"\n",
        "}))\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "salary_missing_by_state = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    STATE_NAME AS state_name,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT ID) AS total_postings,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NOT NULL\n",
        "             AND ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED > 0\n",
        "        THEN ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_available,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "             OR ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "        THEN ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_missing,\n",
        "    ROUND(\n",
        "        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "            WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "                 OR ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "            THEN ID\n",
        "        END) / COUNT(DISTINCT ID) * 100,\n",
        "        2\n",
        "    ) AS missing_salary_percent\n",
        "FROM raw_jobs_clean\n",
        "WHERE STATE_NAME IS NOT NULL\n",
        "GROUP BY STATE_NAME\n",
        "HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ID) >= 100\n",
        "ORDER BY missing_salary_percent DESC\n",
        "LIMIT 20\n",
        "\"\"\").toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "display(style_table(salary_missing_by_state, {\n",
        "    \"total_postings\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_available\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_missing\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"missing_salary_percent\": \"{:.2f}%\"\n",
        "}))\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "salary_missing_by_industry = spark.sql(\"\"\"\n",
        "SELECT\n",
        "    NAICS_2022_6_NAME AS industry,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT ID) AS total_postings,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NOT NULL\n",
        "             AND ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED > 0\n",
        "        THEN ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_available,\n",
        "    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "        WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "             OR ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "        THEN ID\n",
        "    END) AS salary_missing,\n",
        "    ROUND(\n",
        "        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE\n",
        "            WHEN ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED IS NULL\n",
        "                 OR ANALYSIS_SALARY_INDUSTRY_IMPUTED <= 0\n",
        "            THEN ID\n",
        "        END) / COUNT(DISTINCT ID) * 100,\n",
        "        2\n",
        "    ) AS missing_salary_percent\n",
        "FROM raw_jobs_clean\n",
        "WHERE NAICS_2022_6_NAME IS NOT NULL\n",
        "GROUP BY NAICS_2022_6_NAME\n",
        "HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ID) >= 100\n",
        "ORDER BY missing_salary_percent DESC\n",
        "LIMIT 20\n",
        "\"\"\").toPandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "display(style_table(salary_missing_by_industry, {\n",
        "    \"total_postings\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_available\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"salary_missing\": \"{:,.0f}\",\n",
        "    \"missing_salary_percent\": \"{:.2f}%\"\n",
        "}))"
      ],
      "id": "9e7d4d43",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "**Insight:** Salary missingness remains important even after industry-median imputation. The imputed salary variable improves coverage, but missingness can still vary by AI classification, remote type, state, and industry. Salary-based results should therefore be interpreted with this remaining missingness in mind.\n",
        "\n",
        "## 5. Remote Type Distribution"
      ],
      "id": "23889c75"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
